Reasoning: The paper describes the development of an application for federated search of legal documents, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as entity recognition and free text search. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hierarchical data structures and network graphs, which could fall under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DL) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the collection and analysis of large amounts of data, which could also fall under the Database (cs.DB) sub-category.
